The paper deals with privacy concerns in face images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and security (cs.CR) research. The proposed method involves the use of machine learning techniques, specifically Semi-Adversarial Networks (SAN), which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the generalizability of SANs, which is a common concern in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
